      "note": "Most of the commentators explain the \"thus\" or \"thus it is\" (kadhalika) as referring to the earlier prophets, namely, \"Thus, [or \"in like manner\"] as We sent prophets before thee, O Muhammad, We have now sent thee ...\", etc. It seems to me, however, that this speculative interpolation is unnecessary, and that the adverb \"thus\" connects directly with the preceding statement that God \"guides unto Himself all who turn unto Him\": in other words, the \"thus\" qualifies Muhammad's mission as an instrument of God's guidance. (This is, apparently, how Tabari understands the above phrase.)"
